My father passed away 50 days ago and I haven't had the motivation nor time to do as much as I used to. I'm slowly stepping out to start creating and doing art in order to help me cherish the memories I have of him. It's been really hard to lose someone so suddenly, especially someone who has such a major impact on shaping the individual that I am today.  I miss my dad terribly, but he still lives on thru his two sons. Thank you for always being there for us, I hope you can rest easy now. I love you forever dad.

Although I know that you're not here anymore, I'll still paint you these artworks. I want you to know what is going on in my life.

Happy Father's day 爸爸. Hope you're out there in the great beyond seeing and experiencing things that you get to tell me all about when we meet again.

Thanks to @azuubanana for the amazing Sketching in Blender class over at @warriorartcamp 

#blender #sketchinginblender #blender3d #blenderart #cosmos #whaleshark #sailboat #visdev #spirits #thegreatbeyond #artoflei

With LBX coming up, I'm happy to share that I'll be tabling with the beautifully talented @jenniferwang.arts ✨

You can find us at Table 532. I'll have a few limited prints and also bringing some original plein air paintings for folks to check out. Swing by and say hello, we'd be happy to meet everyone 🙌

#lightboxexpo #lightboxexpo2023 #lbx2023 #convention #artoflei

A tribute to my uncle and my dad, we miss you two so much. The Lei family now is missing a pair of tiger and dragon. 2023 and forward just won’t feel the same without you two. We hope you’re in a better place riding the lightning and laughing thunderously.
